  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lao PDR Shelter Recovery 2018</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM will focus its efforts on the return and recovery needs, as well as the health and well-being of those displaced and most affected by the flooding in Lao People&apos;s Democratic Republic, particularly in the villages hit by the dam collapse and subsequent flooding and those in the seven evacuation centres/collective centres identified to date. To ensure a comprehensive response, IOM will includesupport directly to the Shelter Cluster that it co-leads, particularly for coordination and Information Management through the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) in order to better track and report on the people in evacuation centres and their return and/or relocation process as wellas the basic needs for services and assistance at the most affected villages as they recover (Shelter activities).</narrative>
  </description>
